With our cars loaded with: caps and gowns, yard signs, student’s belongings, and portfolios, Karen Higginbotham and I set out yesterday and today to see our precious kindergarteners. We had the pleasure of visiting and seeing all 19 of our kindergarten students. Although they didn’t get their traditional graduation ceremony, they were able to celebrate their accomplishments and bright futures with their families.

Jerry Sarah Henson was our last stop today. I recorded his excitement to share.

shared_text:
Traci Balzer-Cochenour added a new video to the album: Andrew & Dylan’s Graduation.
May 22 at 12:28 AM ·

**Graduation ceremony video**
We had a rainy day for Andrew and Dylan’s graduation but it was still a wonderful afternoon. Thank you to everyone who came and shared in their special day. Also, thank you to Neil, Robie, & Grant for making sure each senior was able to have a memorable graduation moment. I also want to thank my mom, Jeanie Balzer, for her wonderful words of scripture and prayer and how truly special it was that she could be part of Andrew and Dylan’s day. Lastly, a huge thanks to my aunt, Darla Colegrove Mummey for taking all of the photos and shooting the video. It was such a big relief to be able to enjoy the moment and not have to fumble with my camera.
🧡🦅🤎

We had a rainy day for Andrew and Dylan’s graduation but it was still a wonderful afternoon. Thank you to everyone who came and shared in their special day. Also, thank you to Neil, Robie, & Grant for making sure each senior was able to have a memorable graduation moment. I also want to thank my mom, Jeanie Balzer, for her wonderful words of scripture and prayer and how truly special it was that she could be part of Andrew and Dylan’s day. Lastly, a huge thanks to my aunt, Darla Colegrove Mummey for taking all of the photos and shooting the video. It was such a big relief to be able to enjoy the moment and not have to fumble with my camera.
🧡🦅🤎

post_text:
Today was a huge success for the Eastern archery team!! 259 archers from 16 schools shot in two tournaments at Eastern Middle/High School today... the Appalachian Archery Conference (AAC) bullseye tournament and a 3D fun shoot.

Also, big day for the Eastern Middle School team who earned a 3rd place finish!

Top individuals for the day...

Madilen Day finished 2nd in MS girls in the conference tournament and 3rd in MS girls in the 3D tournament. Also finished 3rd out all 259 archers in all divisions!

Gavin Cook finished 11th in the conference tournament and 5th in the 3D tournament in HS boys!

Christian Canaday finished 9th in the 3D tournament in HS boys!

Gracie Long finished 16th in the conference tournament and 4th in the 3D tournament in MS girls!

Riley McCoy finished 6th in the 3D tournament!

Brad Long finished 16th in HS boys!

Abigail Medeiros finished 18th in MS girls!

Gracie Turner finished 20th in HS girls!
